	<div class="commentBody">
		<div id="comment_body_64522665"><p>They can send a company representative - must be management or above (able to "represent" the company).<br>Typically they will not bother.  If they no-show they lose by default.  If they send someone, they still probably lose, and they are out the cost of the person's time.<br>You can appeal if you are sued and lose, but not if you initiate the suit and lose.  Also you cannot appeal a default judgement.</p></div>
	</div>

	<div class="commentSub" id="comment_sub_64522665">

